Two children have been brutally murdered in Ivory Park and Orange Farm in Gauteng. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng provincial police is investigating a case of murder after an 11-year-old was brutally murdered in Ivory Park, Gauteng. The 11-year-old went missing on the 10th of April and the body was found in a veld two days later. Visiting the family, Gauteng Community Safety MEC, Faith Mazibuko, appealed to anyone who has information to come forward. "We wish to call upon the community to also help us, because it's time like these where we need each other," she said. Another body of a five-year-old child has been found in Orange farm. The child was found in a tavern between a refrigerator and crates.